The [documentation for `signInWithEmailAndPassword`](https://pub.dev/documentation/firebase_auth/latest/firebase_auth/FirebaseAuth/signInWithEmailAndPassword.html) lists all possible errors:

 * `ERROR_INVALID_EMAIL`

 * `ERROR_WRONG_PASSWORD`

 * `ERROR_USER_NOT_FOUND`

 * `ERROR_USER_DISABLED`

 * `ERROR_TOO_MANY_REQUESTS`

 * `ERROR_OPERATION_NOT_ALLOWED`

Now, you can test for these in your `try`-`catch`:

```dart
try {
  FirebaseAuth.instance.signInWithEmailAndPassword(...); // Your signin call.
} on PlatformException catch (e) {
  switch (e.code) {
    case &#39;ERROR_WRONG_PASSWORD&#39;:
      // Handle wrong password.
      break;
    // Add other cases.
    default:
      break;
  }
}
```

Note that the `catch` block I added only catches `PlatformException`s. If you expect to see other exceptions, you might want to add another general `catch` block or `on` specific exceptions.

